<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FF56FA2D185E9EC0" authority="Faure" authorityName="Faure" authorityYear="1933" box="[151,352,1485,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FF56FA2D185E9EC0" bold="true" box="[151,352,1485,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FF56FA2D18309EC0" bold="true" box="[151,270,1485,1512]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Idiothrips</emphasis>
Faure
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB03699882C4730FF56F9F51B7F9DCC" blockId="3.[151,1437,1557,1764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
This genus comprises only two species which are reported from Africa and Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B68882C4730FBF1F9F51DC99D07" accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" box="[1072,1271,1557,1583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B68882C4730FACBF9F61CA29D07" author="Faure" box="[1290,1436,1557,1584]" firstAuthor="Faure" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref6172" refString="Faure, J. C. (1933) New genera and species of Thysanoptera from South Africa. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 28, 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1933">Faure (1933)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FECDF9DA18549D7B" authorityName="Faure" authorityYear="1933" box="[268,362,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FECDF9DA18549D7B" box="[268,362,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3187609882C4730FE75F9D91B769D7B" box="[436,584,1593,1619]" name="South Africa" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, and this species was subsequently reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F3187609882C4730FB51F9D91DF49D7B" box="[1168,1226,1593,1619]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">India</collectingCountry>
(Ananthakrishnan 1964) and then from 
<collectingRegion id="49CBF87B882C4730FE4EF9BE1B679D5F" box="[399,601,1629,1656]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Kerman province</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3187609882C4730FD10F9BE1BC09D50" box="[721,766,1630,1656]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B68882C4730FCCEF9BD1D639D5F" author="Kheyrandish Koshkoei" box="[783,1117,1629,1655]" firstAuthor="Kheyrandish Koshkoei" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" refId="ref6423" refString="Kheyrandish Koshkoei, M. (2000) Faunistic survey of Thysanoptera in Kerman and study of population density of active species on rose. M. Sc. Thesis, College of Agriculture, Tarbiat Modarres University, Tehran, Iran, 137 pp. [In Persian with English summary]" type="book" year="2000">Kheyrandish Koshkoei 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B68882C4730FBB3F9BD1C289D5F" author="Minaei" box="[1138,1302,1629,1655]" firstAuthor="Minaei" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref6523" refString="Minaei, K. (2013) The Phlaeothrips - lineage of fungus feeding thrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae) in Iran with a new species of Hindsiothrips. Zootaxa, 3599 (3), 279 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3599.3.5" type="journal article" year="2013">Minaei (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FA4DF9BE19E49DB3" authorityName="Faure" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FA4DF9BE19E49DB3" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13342A1C882C4730FF2AF961180E9DB3" box="[235,304,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 1â€“12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,184,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[197,1390,179,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1â€“12. Fungus feeding thrips species of Iran (1) Hindsiothrips sisakhti (female); (2) Idiothrips bellus (female); (3) Hoplandrothrips bidens (female); (4) Liophloeothrips arganicus (female); (5) Hoplothrips (female); (6) Cephalothrips monilicornis (female); (7) Cephalothrips coxalis (female); (8) Allothrips bournieri (female); (9) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (female); (10) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (male); (11) Pseudocryptothrips meridionalis (female); (12) Megathrips flavipes (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3364946/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) in 
<collectingRegion id="49CBF87B882C4730FE9EF96218C29DB3" box="[351,508,1665,1692]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fars province</collectingRegion>
, and one female has been collected from leaf litter of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FBA7F9621DFA9DB4" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1126,1220,1666,1692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FBA7F9621DFA9DB4" box="[1126,1220,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. The only other species in the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FE42F9461B159D97" authorityName="zur Strassen" authorityYear="1968" box="[387,555,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maghrebinus">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FE42F9461B159D97" box="[387,555,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. maghrebinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains known from a single female taken in flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D1A882C4730FB68F9451CA29D97" box="[1193,1436,1701,1727]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Phillyrea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="B97BEA8B882C4730FB68F9451CA29D97" box="[1193,1436,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Phillyrea angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Asni, 
<collectingCountry id="F3187609882C4730FF35F92A18679DCC" box="[244,345,1738,1764]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(zur 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B68882C4730FE55F9291B0A9DCC" author="Strassen, R." box="[404,564,1737,1764]" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 125" part="15" refId="ref7622" refString="zur Strassen, R. (1968) Okologische und zoogeographische Studien uber die-Fransenflugler-Fauna (Ins., Thysanoptera) des sudlichen-Marokko. Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 15, 1 - 125." title="Okologische und zoogeographische Studien uber die-Fransenflugler-Fauna (Ins., Thysanoptera) des sudlichen-Marokko" type="journal article" year="1968">Strassen 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
